From 5fd40f0eff5badc9977317e4d368070477fa4b6c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: utzcoz <utzcoz@outlook.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 23:06:28 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] vr: destroy the OpenXR input helper before the session on
 Linux

Entering and exiting an immersive-vr session repeatedly crashed the XR utility
process (SIGSEGV) on Linux/Monado, taking down the session and -- after enough
cycles -- the browser.

OpenXrApiWrapper::Uninitialize() called xrDestroySession() and only afterwards
Reset(), which destroys the input helper. But each OpenXrController creates
action spaces (and a hand tracker) via xrCreateActionSpace(session_, ...); those
are children of the session. Destroying the session frees its child spaces, so
the later ~OpenXrController then called xrDestroySpace() on already-freed
handles. On the Monado OpenXR loader that use-after-free dereferences freed,
poisoned handle state and GP-faults. It manifests intermittently (heap-reuse
timing), which is why it took several enter/exit cycles to crash rather than the
first.

Destroy the input helper before xrDestroySession() so xrDestroySpace() runs
while the session -- and its child spaces -- are still valid. Gated to Linux;
other runtimes tolerate the original order, so Windows and Android are unchanged.

Verified against Monado (AMD RADV): 15 enter/exit cycles logged
"XR_ERROR_HANDLE_INVALID: xrDestroySpace" plus a SIGSEGV every cycle before the
change; 0 crashes across 23 cycles after it, with sessions confirmed entering
and exiting and the controllers active.
---
 device/vr/openxr/openxr_api_wrapper.cc | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/device/vr/openxr/openxr_api_wrapper.cc b/device/vr/openxr/openxr_api_wrapper.cc
index 7fdd2f6aa1312..a519f48b0105d 100644
--- a/device/vr/openxr/openxr_api_wrapper.cc
+++ b/device/vr/openxr/openxr_api_wrapper.cc
@@ -236,6 +236,14 @@ XrResult OpenXrApiWrapper::ShutdownSession() {
 void OpenXrApiWrapper::Uninitialize() {
   // The instance is owned by the OpenXRDevice, so don't destroy it here.
 
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_LINUX)
+  // Destroy the input helper before xrDestroySession(): its controllers own
+  // action spaces that are children of the session, and xrDestroySession()
+  // frees them. Destroying it afterwards (via Reset() below) would call
+  // xrDestroySpace() on freed handles, which crashes the Monado loader.
+  input_helper_.reset();
+#endif  // BUILDFLAG(IS_LINUX)
+
   // Destroying an session in OpenXr also destroys all child objects of that
   // instance (including the swapchain, and spaces objects),
   // so they don't need to be manually destroyed.
-- 
2.53.0

